---
import MadeByKaj from '../components/MadeByKaj.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
	title="Found in Space"
	description="Explore the stars near the Sun through guided journeys, clear explanations, and open technical notes built on measurements from ESA's Gaia mission."
>
	<header class="site-header">
		<a class="wordmark" href={basePath} aria-label="Found in Space home">
			<img class="wordmark__mark" src={`${basePath}robbie.svg`} alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
			<span class="wordmark__text">
				<span class="wordmark__title">Found in Space</span>
				<span class="wordmark__meta">Explore the nearby stars</span>
			</span>
		</a>
		<nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary">
			<a href="#explore">Explore</a>
			<a href="#learn">Learn</a>
			<a href="#build">Build</a>
			<a href="#about">About</a>
		</nav>
	</header>

	<main class="page">
		<section class="hero">
			<p class="eyebrow">A guide to the stars near the Sun</p>
			<h1>Start with the night sky you know. Discover the space it hides.</h1>
			<p class="intro">
				Found in Space is a growing home for exploring the solar neighbourhood: the stars nearest
				to our Sun. Using measurements from ESA's Gaia mission, it turns catalogues and
				visualisations into guided journeys, clear explanations, and tools people can actually
				learn from.
			</p>
			<div class="hero__actions">
				<a class="button button--primary" href="#explore">Take a first look</a>
				<a class="button button--ghost" href="#build">How it's built</a>
			</div>
			<div class="hero__note">
				<p>
					Still early, but already taking shape as part exhibit, part classroom, part lab.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section-grid" aria-label="Choose your path">
			<article class="panel panel--accent" id="explore">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Explore</p>
				<h2>Follow guided journeys from familiar skies into depth, distance, and scale.</h2>
				<p>
					Start with constellations, bright stars, and recognisable patterns, then see what
					changes when those same stars are placed in three-dimensional space.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="panel" id="learn">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Learn</p>
				<h2>Turn curiosity into understanding with clear explainers and reusable learning routes.</h2>
				<p>
					This is for self-directed learners, students, and educators who want more than a pretty
					simulation: plain-language concepts, structured pathways, and activities that can grow
					into teaching material.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="panel" id="build">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Build</p>
				<h2>See how astronomical measurements become something you can explore in a browser.</h2>
				<p>
					Behind the scenes are source catalogues, data cleaning, spatial indexing, and a
					browser-based viewer. The technical side will stay open, inspectable, and explained in
					human terms.
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>

		<section class="story">
			<div class="story__lead">
				<p class="eyebrow">Why this project exists</p>
				<h2>Wonder is a great starting point, but it should lead somewhere.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="story__body">
				<p>
					Most people meet astronomy through images, headlines, or the visible sky. That first
					spark matters. Found in Space is about carrying it further: helping people move from
					"that's beautiful" to "I understand what I'm looking at."
				</p>
				<p>
					The solar neighbourhood is a good place to begin because scale becomes easier to feel when
					it starts close to home. From there we can talk honestly about distance, measurement,
					structure, and uncertainty without losing the sense of wonder that brought people here in
					the first place.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="bands">
			<article class="band">
				<p class="band__label">Featured journey</p>
				<h3>What constellations hide about 3D space</h3>
				<p>
					A familiar pattern in the night sky becomes an entry point for perspective, parallax, and
					the fact that stars which look adjacent from Earth may be separated by huge distances.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="band">
				<p class="band__label">Choose your path</p>
				<h3>Explore, learn, or build</h3>
				<p>
					Start with an experience, follow it with an explanation, or open up the technical stack.
					Each route is different, but they are designed to connect.
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>

		<section class="about" id="about">
			<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
			<h2>A labour of love for astronomy, data, and exploration.</h2>
			<p>
				Found in Space grows out of Kaj's long-standing love of astronomy, data science, and the joy of
				exploration. It is an attempt to bring those things together in a form that feels open,
				playful, and genuinely useful: something people can wander through, learn from, and build
				on.
			</p>
			<p>
				The hope is simple: to make the nearby
				universe feel a little more legible, and a little more alive, for anyone who arrives here
				curious.
			</p>
		</section>

		<MadeByKaj />
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.site-header {
		position: sticky;
		top: 0;
		z-index: 4;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1rem;
		max-width: calc(var(--fis-max-width) + 3rem);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 1rem 1.5rem 0;
		background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(7, 17, 31, 0.88), rgba(7, 17, 31, 0));
		backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
	}

	.wordmark {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.85rem;
		padding: 0.65rem 0.85rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: rgba(8, 15, 27, 0.68);
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line);
		box-shadow: var(--fis-shadow);
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.wordmark__mark {
		width: 2.25rem;
		height: 2.25rem;
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		object-fit: contain;
	}

	.wordmark__text {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.1rem;
	}

	.wordmark__title {
		font-size: 1rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	.wordmark__meta {
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		color: var(--fis-text-muted);
	}

	.site-nav {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.55rem;
		font-size: 0.96rem;
	}

	.site-nav a {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		min-height: 2.55rem;
		padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: rgba(8, 15, 27, 0.62);
		border: 1px solid rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.14);
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition:
			transform 160ms ease,
			background-color 160ms ease,
			border-color 160ms ease,
			color 160ms ease;
	}

	.site-nav a:hover {
		transform: translateY(-1px);
		background: rgba(15, 28, 50, 0.82);
		border-color: rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.32);
		color: var(--fis-text);
	}

	.page {
		position: relative;
		min-height: 100vh;
		max-width: var(--fis-max-width);
		padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 5rem;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.18em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 4.2rem 0 2.4rem;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	h3 {
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.25rem);
		line-height: 0.95;
		max-width: 12ch;
	}

	.intro {
		max-width: 46rem;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
		margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
	}

	.hero__actions {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.85rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.button {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		min-height: 2.9rem;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.15rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-size: 0.98rem;
		transition:
			transform 160ms ease,
			box-shadow 160ms ease,
			border-color 160ms ease;
	}

	.button:hover {
		transform: translateY(-1px);
	}

	.button--primary {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f2c879 0%, #f3deac 100%);
		color: #0d1524;
		box-shadow: 0 16px 30px rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.18);
	}

	.button--ghost {
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line-strong);
		background: rgba(9, 18, 33, 0.5);
		color: var(--fis-text);
	}

	.hero__note,
	.panel,
	.band,
	.about {
		background: var(--fis-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line);
		border-radius: var(--fis-radius);
		backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
		box-shadow: var(--fis-shadow);
	}

	.hero__note {
		max-width: 36rem;
		padding: 1.05rem 1.15rem;
		border-color: rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.16);
	}

	.section-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 2rem 0 4rem;
	}

	.panel {
		padding: 1.45rem;
	}

	.panel--accent {
		background:
			linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.12), rgba(10, 20, 36, 0.78)),
			var(--fis-panel);
	}

	.panel__eyebrow,
	.band__label {
		margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	.story {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		align-items: start;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.story__lead h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
		line-height: 1.02;
		max-width: 11ch;
	}

	.story__body {
		padding-top: 0.35rem;
	}

	.bands {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.band {
		padding: 1.45rem;
		background: var(--fis-panel-strong);
	}

	.about {
		padding: 1.6rem;
		max-width: 48rem;
	}

	h2 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1.75rem;
		line-height: 1.1;
	}

	h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		line-height: 1.15;
	}

	p {
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
	}

	section p + p {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.about a {
		color: var(--fis-gold);
		text-decoration-color: rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.46);
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.section-grid,
		.story,
		.bands {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.story__lead h2 {
			max-width: none;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.site-header {
			align-items: flex-start;
			flex-direction: column;
			padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
		}

		.page {
			padding-top: 2.25rem;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 14vw, 4.2rem);
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.intro {
			font-size: 1.05rem;
		}
	}
</style>
